headline: U.S. Senate candidate leads first lawsuit challenging dissolution of Disney Worlds Reedy Creek
author: Skyler Swisher
sentences: The lawsuit filed this week in federal court is the first legal challenge to ending The Walt Disney Co.s private government in Florida.
They are represented by William Sanchez, a Miami lawyer and Democratic candidate for U.S. Senate.
The plaintiffs are Michael and Edward Foronda of Kissimmee and Vivian Gorsky of Orange County.
Three Central Florida taxpayers represented by a lawyer running for U.S. Senate are suing Gov.
Ron DeSantis over the dissolution of Disney Worlds Reedy Creek Improvement District.
